1
00:00:00,380 --> 00:00:03,500
Mimi and I made our way to Primary
Village, where we found Electmon,

2
00:00:03,680 --> 00:00:05,620
who also resolved to join our ragtag
group.

3
00:00:05,900 --> 00:00:08,680
Knowing Mimi would now be safe,
I made the same decision as Matt,

4
00:00:08,840 --> 00:00:11,015
to go find out what kind
of person I am, and make

5
00:00:11,016 --> 00:00:13,120
sure I can be counted
on when the time arrives.

6
00:00:13,480 --> 00:00:15,817
Meanwhile, Ty and his crew
made it to the top of Spiral

7
00:00:15,818 --> 00:00:18,580
Mountain, where they came
face to face with Lady Debumon.

8
00:00:18,880 --> 00:00:21,691
Sora and TK set out to
find the rest of us for the final

9
00:00:21,692 --> 00:00:24,860
confrontation, while Ty and Izzy
stayed behind to keep Piedmon busy.

10
00:00:25,140 --> 00:00:27,180
Do you think he'd mind rescheduling our
destruction?

11
00:00:27,260 --> 00:00:28,260
Guess not.

12
00:00:49,850 --> 00:00:56,670
Change into digital champions to save the
digital world!

13
00:00:57,390 --> 00:01:00,530
Digimon, digital monsters, Digimon are the
champions!

14
00:01:01,430 --> 00:01:04,530
Digimon, digital monsters, Digimon are the
champions!

15
00:01:07,570 --> 00:01:09,190
Digimon are the champions!

16
00:01:26,650 --> 00:01:29,350
We've looked everywhere, Gomomon,
but we still can't find Matt.

17
00:01:29,630 --> 00:01:31,970
Maybe your harmonica playing is keeping
him in hiding.

18
00:01:32,770 --> 00:01:34,190
Hmm, everybody's a critic.

19
00:01:34,191 --> 00:01:35,850
Hey, Joe, look over there!

20
00:01:36,290 --> 00:01:37,290
What is it?

21
00:01:38,550 --> 00:01:39,550
It's Matt's boat!

22
00:01:39,730 --> 00:01:40,730
He must be close by!

23
00:01:41,090 --> 00:01:44,470
But we have no idea of when he left it,
or if he was using it at all!

24
00:01:44,710 --> 00:01:45,990
Come on, we better keep looking!

25
00:01:46,650 --> 00:01:47,810
Don't be such a downer!

26
00:01:47,890 --> 00:01:51,630
This is our first clue in a long time, and
I want to see a little get-up in Golemon!

27
00:01:51,890 --> 00:01:53,841
I guess I'm still pessimistic,
because when we

28
00:01:53,941 --> 00:01:55,590
found Matt's harmonica,
it let us know where.

29
00:01:55,850 --> 00:01:57,570
But you're right, he could be nearby.

30
00:01:57,571 --> 00:01:58,810
Now that's a spirit.

31
00:01:58,990 --> 00:02:00,630
Joe, you've become a real man lately!

32
00:02:00,850 --> 00:02:02,090
Oh, I get it now.

33
00:02:02,290 --> 00:02:04,830
So you're saying that I wasn't a real man
before, huh?

34
00:02:05,130 --> 00:02:07,470
Are you mad enough not to laugh when I
tickle you?

35
00:02:08,710 --> 00:02:09,710
Mega Claw!

36
00:02:17,250 --> 00:02:18,410
I think we won!

37
00:02:20,470 --> 00:02:22,550
Thank you for the sparring match,
WarGreymon.

38
00:02:22,650 --> 00:02:23,970
Now I'm ready for the main event.

39
00:02:25,130 --> 00:02:26,130
Oh no!

40
00:02:26,970 --> 00:02:29,410
Once upon a time, there were these
digi-destined.

41
00:02:30,030 --> 00:02:32,070
And then Paidmon destroyed them all.

42
00:02:32,190 --> 00:02:32,550
The end.

43
00:02:32,551 --> 00:02:34,671
No offense to your
storytelling skills, but I'd

44
00:02:34,672 --> 00:02:36,310
like it better if your
ending were different.

45
00:02:36,390 --> 00:02:37,010
It will be!

46
00:02:37,310 --> 00:02:39,030
We can't win unless we're all together!

47
00:02:39,970 --> 00:02:41,070
Where are they?

48
00:02:43,410 --> 00:02:45,530
The digi-vice isn't responding at all!

49
00:02:46,070 --> 00:02:47,410
I hope we find them soon!

50
00:02:47,411 --> 00:02:48,470
I'm getting airsick!

51
00:02:48,790 --> 00:02:50,250
We'll never find them all!

52
00:02:50,550 --> 00:02:52,450
The digital world is too big!

53
00:02:52,690 --> 00:02:53,850
They could be anywhere!

54
00:02:56,990 --> 00:02:57,990
Hey, Sora!

55
00:02:58,370 --> 00:02:58,750
What?

56
00:02:59,030 --> 00:03:01,230
We'll be able to find Matt and the others,
right?

57
00:03:01,231 --> 00:03:03,010
Should I tell him the truth?

58
00:03:03,630 --> 00:03:04,630
Well, Sora?

59
00:03:05,290 --> 00:03:07,420
The only thing I can say, TK, is...

60
00:03:09,510 --> 00:03:10,510
Are you alright?

61
00:03:10,850 --> 00:03:12,290
You're not crying, are you?

62
00:03:12,630 --> 00:03:13,910
Just something in my eye.

63
00:03:14,050 --> 00:03:14,430
Don't worry.

64
00:03:14,590 --> 00:03:15,590
We'll find them, TK.

65
00:03:17,590 --> 00:03:18,590
Hmm...

66
00:03:19,870 --> 00:03:21,870
We'll find the others because we have to.

67
00:03:22,070 --> 00:03:24,550
Unless we fight as a team, we'll never
defeat Paidmon.

68
00:03:24,790 --> 00:03:26,870
We can't let him destroy the digital
world!

69
00:03:29,950 --> 00:03:31,070
Tear up more!

70
00:03:39,830 --> 00:03:40,590
He's tough.

71
00:03:40,830 --> 00:03:41,730
We should all fight.

72
00:03:41,830 --> 00:03:42,950
Everyone stay where you are!

73
00:03:43,030 --> 00:03:44,310
But Ty, why not?

74
00:03:44,710 --> 00:03:47,630
The Digimon are still too tired from our
fight with Lady Devimon.

75
00:03:47,830 --> 00:03:51,170
We have to wait until we're at full
strength when Matt and the others rejoin us.

76
00:03:51,171 --> 00:03:52,690
I hope it's soon.

77
00:03:55,510 --> 00:03:55,950
Matt?

78
00:03:56,490 --> 00:03:57,490
Yeah, Paidmon?

79
00:03:57,630 --> 00:04:00,190
Maybe we've been traveling in this
direction a little too long.

80
00:04:00,410 --> 00:04:02,390
This cave is starting to give me the
creeps.

81
00:04:02,570 --> 00:04:04,070
Let's hurry up and get out of here.

82
00:04:04,390 --> 00:04:06,630
I'm still not sure what
you mean by trying to find

83
00:04:06,631 --> 00:04:09,210
yourself, but I'd appreciate
it if you didn't look in here.

84
00:04:09,630 --> 00:04:10,070
Sure.

85
00:04:10,490 --> 00:04:11,490
Whatever.

86
00:04:13,990 --> 00:04:14,990
See everybody?

87
00:04:15,090 --> 00:04:16,090
I told you I'd be back.

88
00:04:16,210 --> 00:04:17,930
I can take care of myself just fine.

89
00:04:19,990 --> 00:04:21,290
I've been living a lie.

90
00:04:22,030 --> 00:04:23,110
You're not a real blonde?

91
00:04:24,650 --> 00:04:28,890
I kept saying TK needed me, but really,
I was the one who needed him.

92
00:04:29,110 --> 00:04:30,110
What do you mean?

93
00:04:30,470 --> 00:04:34,110
I used to think that my one purpose in
life was to protect my little brother.

94
00:04:35,830 --> 00:04:37,711
But then... You're the man!

95
00:04:37,890 --> 00:04:38,890
Nice going, TK!

96
00:04:38,930 --> 00:04:39,570
Great job, buddy!

97
00:04:39,571 --> 00:04:41,070
We were so worried about you.

98
00:04:41,170 --> 00:04:43,230
Boy, for a little kid, that was a pretty
big escape.

99
00:04:44,930 --> 00:04:46,810
He didn't need me to protect him anymore.

100
00:04:47,410 --> 00:04:50,730
And Ty was much better at acting like a
big brother than I ever was.

101
00:04:51,830 --> 00:04:53,150
But you don't have to act.

102
00:04:54,470 --> 00:04:55,810
You are TK's brother.

103
00:04:55,910 --> 00:04:56,910
Ty isn't.

104
00:04:57,250 --> 00:04:58,250
That's just the point.

105
00:04:58,330 --> 00:04:59,690
I don't act like a brother at all.

106
00:04:59,870 --> 00:05:01,958
And even though it made
me feel good to think that I was

107
00:05:01,959 --> 00:05:04,670
the only one there for him,
in reality, all the kids were.

108
00:05:04,910 --> 00:05:06,290
Let's talk about this outside.

109
00:05:06,530 --> 00:05:08,270
There's something strange about this
place.

110
00:05:08,271 --> 00:05:10,070
That's why Ty made me so mad.

111
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:12,430
I thought he was trying to take TK away
from me.

112
00:05:13,350 --> 00:05:16,010
Ty might be real bossy and hard-headed
sometimes.

113
00:05:16,630 --> 00:05:18,890
But he never treated TK like a child.

114
00:05:19,130 --> 00:05:21,010
Which is how I've always treated him.

115
00:05:21,170 --> 00:05:22,730
But I'm the one who's childish.

116
00:05:23,430 --> 00:05:24,750
Matt, stop putting yourself down.

117
00:05:24,810 --> 00:05:27,690
Sure, you have some teenage angst,
but you've been a great brother to TK.

118
00:05:27,910 --> 00:05:30,910
I used to think Ty never thought about
anyone but himself.

119
00:05:31,490 --> 00:05:33,850
But that actually describes me a lot
better.

120
00:05:37,050 --> 00:05:38,050
Oh, Matt.

121
00:05:39,370 --> 00:05:40,050
Oh, Matt!

122
00:05:40,230 --> 00:05:41,910
I think you'd better take a look at this!

123
00:05:42,350 --> 00:05:43,350
Whatever.

124
00:05:44,430 --> 00:05:45,430
I'm no good.

125
00:05:45,830 --> 00:05:47,770
I can never go back to being their friend.

126
00:05:49,710 --> 00:05:50,710
You have to!

127
00:05:50,790 --> 00:05:52,901
Don't you understand that
if the eight of you don't get

128
00:05:52,902 --> 00:05:55,211
back together, the digital
world will be destroyed forever?

129
00:05:55,510 --> 00:05:59,030
They don't need me, and besides,
seven is a luckier number than eight.

130
00:05:59,031 --> 00:06:00,210
Hey Matt, snap out of it!

131
00:06:00,270 --> 00:06:01,090
Just go away.

132
00:06:01,270 --> 00:06:02,270
I want to be alone.

133
00:06:02,610 --> 00:06:03,610
Come to your senses!

134
00:06:06,670 --> 00:06:07,670
Matt, listen!

135
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:12,900
Ow!

136
00:06:13,100 --> 00:06:14,100
What are you doing?

137
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,160
Are you crazy?

138
00:06:15,340 --> 00:06:16,420
Don't you understand, Matt?

139
00:06:16,460 --> 00:06:18,180
You've got to quit comparing yourself to
Ty.

140
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:18,940
You're not him.

141
00:06:19,140 --> 00:06:20,140
It's like ice cream.

142
00:06:20,220 --> 00:06:21,800
He's vanilla, and you're Rocky Road.

143
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:24,700
But only one of you is TK's real brother,
and it's not him.

144
00:06:24,980 --> 00:06:27,386
No matter how much he
impresses TK, Ty will never be

145
00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:29,700
able to break the bond
that you two brothers share.

146
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:30,840
Come on!

147
00:06:31,460 --> 00:06:35,040
And besides, don't you think it would
break my heart if you weren't here?

148
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:37,171
After all, I didn't wait
my entire life for you

149
00:06:37,172 --> 00:06:39,801
to arrive, just so you
can wallow in self-pity.

150
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:41,040
Huh?

151
00:06:41,280 --> 00:06:41,680
Gabumon.

152
00:06:42,060 --> 00:06:46,540
But Matt, if you really want to be left
alone, then I'll respect your wishes and

153
00:06:46,541 --> 00:06:49,900
disappear, but only if that's what you
really want me to do.

154
00:06:50,580 --> 00:06:51,060
No.

155
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:52,900
I don't really want to be left alone.

156
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:53,680
Sorry.

157
00:06:53,900 --> 00:06:55,220
I never meant to hurt you.

158
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:55,840
Hmm.

159
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:58,720
I've never let anyone get close to me
before.

160
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:01,560
Not since my family split up.

161
00:07:04,540 --> 00:07:06,560
Ever since then, I've been alone.

162
00:07:07,180 --> 00:07:09,768
I figured if my family didn't
want me, then I would just

163
00:07:09,769 --> 00:07:12,160
keep to myself and never
tell anyone what I was feeling.

164
00:07:12,380 --> 00:07:14,460
And I swore I would never let anyone see
me cry.

165
00:07:15,980 --> 00:07:18,900
But really, all I wanted to do was cry.

166
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:19,800
And cry.

167
00:07:20,060 --> 00:07:21,260
I hate being alone.

168
00:07:21,540 --> 00:07:22,660
I'm here for you, Matt.

169
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:24,320
I used to be lonely too.

170
00:07:24,540 --> 00:07:26,976
I wandered around the digital world
without any friends at all.

171
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:29,900
And then after I met you, I knew I'd never
be lonely again.

172
00:07:30,260 --> 00:07:31,320
I know what you mean.

173
00:07:31,540 --> 00:07:32,040
Me too.

174
00:07:32,440 --> 00:07:35,740
After all, you're the main reason I came
to the digital world in the first place.

175
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:40,660
And here I am, lost in this dark, strange
cave, and you're still right by my side.

176
00:07:40,880 --> 00:07:42,580
That's the sign of a true friend.

177
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:43,620
Oh, shucks.

178
00:07:43,621 --> 00:07:45,460
I guess I have friends.

179
00:07:45,660 --> 00:07:47,540
And that includes TK and my mom and dad.

180
00:07:53,300 --> 00:07:55,440
Now I realize I was never really alone.

181
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:56,920
People like me.

182
00:07:57,060 --> 00:07:58,560
They really, really like me.

183
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:00,900
Matt, look!

184
00:08:01,100 --> 00:08:02,100
What is it?

185
00:08:02,300 --> 00:08:03,920
It's been around you this whole time.

186
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,800
You mean you haven't noticed it until now?

187
00:08:06,020 --> 00:08:07,020
Not at all.

188
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:08,220
It was weird.

189
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:11,040
The more you talked about being alone,
the bigger that thing got.

190
00:08:12,620 --> 00:08:13,760
It's pitch black.

191
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:18,540
That's exactly the feeling I had in my
heart just a minute ago.

192
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:20,020
I know what it is.

193
00:08:20,320 --> 00:08:21,320
Please tell me.

194
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:26,440
It's... It's the darkness that I've been
carrying around with me this whole time.

195
00:08:27,340 --> 00:08:30,000
The darkness that's been buried in my
heart.

196
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:32,600
Oh, Gabumon.

197
00:08:32,940 --> 00:08:34,940
Now it's ready to swallow me up whole.

198
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,480
Like Jonah and the whale?

199
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:38,538
I have a feeling that
if I didn't recognize it

200
00:08:38,539 --> 00:08:40,801
just now, it would have
taken over my whole life.

201
00:08:40,920 --> 00:08:42,520
But I'm not gonna let that happen.

202
00:08:42,940 --> 00:08:43,160
Hmm?

203
00:08:43,161 --> 00:08:46,060
It can't hurt me because I'm not alone
anymore.

204
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:47,500
That's the spirit.

205
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:49,720
I wanna thank you, Gabumon.

206
00:08:50,420 --> 00:08:51,200
Don't mention it.

207
00:08:51,260 --> 00:08:52,336
That's what friends are for.

208
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:53,720
Besides, I should be thanking you.

209
00:08:53,780 --> 00:08:55,620
You're the best friend a Digimon ever had.

210
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:58,100
Let's make a promise
that we'll always be

211
00:08:58,101 --> 00:09:00,300
there for each other
no matter what happens.

212
00:09:00,700 --> 00:09:02,500
Gabumon and Matt, friends for life.

213
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:06,020
What do you say?

214
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:06,820
Do we have a deal?

215
00:09:06,940 --> 00:09:08,200
A handshake makes it official.

216
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:09,720
Will a pawshake do?

217
00:09:09,920 --> 00:09:12,120
And I promise not to complain anymore
either.

218
00:09:12,121 --> 00:09:13,500
Don't start that again.

219
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:16,300
If you're upset about something,
you should get it off your chest.

220
00:09:17,220 --> 00:09:21,020
Alright, if you insist, I'll still
complain once in a while, but only to you.

221
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:22,480
Huh?

222
00:09:24,040 --> 00:09:25,941
Correct me if I'm wrong
on this one, Matt, but

223
00:09:25,942 --> 00:09:28,261
weren't we just in a big
dark cave a minute ago?

224
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:30,560
That's right, and we were completely lost.

225
00:09:31,020 --> 00:09:31,420
Hey!

226
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:32,780
Matt!

227
00:09:33,300 --> 00:09:34,300
Over here!

228
00:09:35,380 --> 00:09:36,380
It's Joe!

229
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:45,580
Who's the man now?

230
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:46,800
I told you I'd find him!

231
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:49,100
I never doubted you for a single minute,
Joe.

232
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:50,320
What's going on?

233
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:52,805
I said to myself, Joe,
I said, just follow your

234
00:09:52,806 --> 00:09:54,941
own path and sooner or
later you'll run into Matt.

235
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,740
I'm just glad it happened before I
retired.

236
00:09:57,060 --> 00:09:58,060
I see.

237
00:09:58,880 --> 00:09:59,880
Oh, that's right.

238
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:00,400
I forgot.

239
00:10:00,660 --> 00:10:01,000
Here.

240
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:02,580
It's your harmonica, isn't it?

241
00:10:03,700 --> 00:10:04,760
Hm.

242
00:10:05,520 --> 00:10:06,540
Thanks, Joe.

243
00:10:07,700 --> 00:10:08,700
Mm-hmm.

244
00:10:11,680 --> 00:10:12,740
Trimpsons!

245
00:10:20,580 --> 00:10:22,160
Wargrimmon's exhausted!

246
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:23,700
I can't watch anymore!

247
00:10:24,280 --> 00:10:25,380
Stay tough!

248
00:10:32,580 --> 00:10:34,460
Please, Izzy, let me help Wargrimmon!

249
00:10:34,740 --> 00:10:35,740
No!

250
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:36,800
Wargrimmon needs help!

251
00:10:37,020 --> 00:10:37,680
Come on, Matt!

252
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:38,840
Where are you?

253
00:10:44,380 --> 00:10:45,460
Look down there!

254
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,460
That's Matt's boat!

255
00:10:49,520 --> 00:10:50,560
But where's...

256
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:54,300
I hope he's not hurt somewhere.

257
00:10:55,820 --> 00:10:57,200
We'll never find him.

258
00:10:57,380 --> 00:10:58,420
What are we going to do?

259
00:10:58,880 --> 00:10:59,880
TK's right.

260
00:11:00,020 --> 00:11:01,980
Maybe we should go back and help the
others fight.

261
00:11:02,740 --> 00:11:03,180
No.

262
00:11:03,540 --> 00:11:06,020
